=== New Tables ===
deal_notes: tenant-scoped, RLS, note_type IN (note, call_log), append-only in this item
deal_activity_log: tenant-scoped, RLS, system event stream, separate from user notes

=== New RPCs ===
create_deal_note_v1(p_deal_id uuid, p_note_type text, p_content text)
  - SECURITY DEFINER, authenticated only
  - write lock enforced via check_workspace_write_allowed_v1()
  - writes to deal_notes only
  - note_type validated: note or call_log
list_deal_notes_v1(p_deal_id uuid)
  - STABLE SECURITY DEFINER, authenticated only
  - returns data.notes, newest first
  - includes created_by_name from user_profiles
list_deal_activity_v1(p_deal_id uuid)
  - STABLE SECURITY DEFINER, authenticated only
  - returns data.activity, newest first
  - includes created_by_name from user_profiles

=== Retrofit ===
mark_deal_dead_v1: extended to insert marked_dead row into deal_activity_log after UPDATE
  - same inputs, same envelope, same error codes as prior version
  - no regression to existing behavior

=== Stream Separation ===
create_deal_note_v1 writes to deal_notes only -- NOT mirrored to deal_activity_log
System events (mark_dead) write to deal_activity_log only -- NOT in deal_notes
Proven by test 19: activity count = 3 (2 seeded + 1 mark_dead, 0 from user notes)

